  "title": "FLOOR / WALL TILER",
  "description": "<p>Roles & Responsibilities</p><p><u><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></u><br /></p><p><strong>Surface Preparation</strong></p><p>• Inspect and prepare floors</p><p>• Clean, level, and prime surfaces</p><p>• Install underlayment or waterproofing<br /></p><p><strong>Planning and Layout</strong></p><p>• Measure areas and plan layouts</p><p>• Mark reference lines</p><p>• Estimate materials<br /></p><p><strong>Tile Installation</strong></p><p>• Cut and shape tiles</p><p>• Apply adhesives/mortars</p><p>• Install tiles with proper spacing and level<br /></p><p><strong>Grouting and Finishing</strong></p><p>• Mix and apply grout</p><p>• Clean tile surfaces</p><p>• Seal tiles or grout when needed<br /></p><p><strong>Maintenance and Repair</strong></p><p>• Replace damaged or loose tiles</p><p>• Re-grout worn areas</p><p>• Perform quality checks<br /></p><p><strong>Safety and Compliance</strong></p><p>• Follow safety guidelines</p><p>• Meet project and industry standards</p><p>• Keep work areas clean</p><p><br /><br /></p><p><u><strong>Qualifications and Skills</strong></u></p><p>• Proven tiling experience</p><p>• Ability to read drawings</p><p>• Knowledge of tile tools and materials</p><p>• Good physical stamina and physically fit<br /></p><p><u><strong>Additional Requirements</strong></u></p><p>• Attentive to details, commitment to produce precise, high-quality work</p><p>• Good communication skills.</p>",
